The paper presents an approach to path following for autonomous vehicles, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves synthesizing controllers using control funnel functions, which are mathematical functions that encode the control law and its correctness argument over a mathematical model of the vehicle dynamics. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of a demonstration-based learning algorithm to synthesize the control funnel function suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The implementation of the approach on a physical vehicle suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
